Frequently Asked Questions

You have questions. We have answers. If you need more help please contact us: Customer Service: 888-774-3662 or info@TattooFun.com

General Tattoo Questions:

Are temporary tattoos safe on the skin?
All the temporary tattoos we sell are FDA approved to be placed on the skin.

How long do temporary tattoos last?
Our high quality temporary tattoos last at least 3-5 days, even with daily exposure to showers, swimming and ocean surfing.

How quickly can I get my temporary tattoos?
We ship daily from San Diego. Our standard shipping is US mail, which can take 5 to 7 days to reach the East coast. Priority mail (3 days) is available for $12.00 and Overnight Air is also available for $25.00

 

Custom Tattoo Questions:

How quickly can I get custom temporary tattoos made and delivered?
To keep the cost down, we group our custom runs together and run them beginning Wednesday of each week. All order received by Noon on Tuesday will be in that weeks run and usually ship early the next week.

How are custom tattoos shipped?
Custom temporary tattoos are shipped via FedEx ground, however expedited overnight air, 2-day and 3-day service is available. Standard shipping usually runs about $10, but the cost varies by the size of your order. Please call for a quote for large or expedited orders.

How much do custom temporary tattoos cost?
Custom-made temporary tattoos are very inexpensive and start at just $70 for 1,000 tattoos. (That's just $.07 each).

How many colors?
All colors are included in the low price. Since we run all of our custom temporary tattoos jobs together, there are never any additional charges for extra colors, PMS colors, etc.

What ís the minimum order for custom-made temporary tattoos?
Because custom temporary tattoos are printed on a large press, there is a 1,000 units minimum run. But remember 1,000 2x2 inch tattoos are just $85...total!

Set-up costs?
We never charge a set-up fee. The price you see is the total price, plus about $10 shipping. (Depending on where we are shipping to)

What ís the difference between the tattoo inkjet paper and the commercially made custom tattoos?
The tattoo inkjet paper works great for people that need less than a 100 or so custom temporary tattoos. The paper easy to use and works great, but requires work on your end, such as cutting and peeling the paper.

Reason ís to buy tattoo inkjet paper versus commercially made custom tattoos:

  • You need them in less than a week.
  • You need less than 100 custom tattoos
  • You want to test some designs on people before ordering 1,000 units
